content.text:
Let me analyze the target structure and provide assembly instructions.

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
- The structure consists of 6 blocks in total
- Contains 2 blue rectangular blocks and 4 orange blocks (including a tall central piece and angled roof pieces)
- Single layer base configuration with vertical extensions

Block Identification from Dictionary:
- Center tall orange cylinder: Block 4
- Blue rectangular blocks on sides: Block 2 (used twice)
- Right triangular roof piece: Block 11
- Left triangular roof pieces: Block 13 and Block 15

Assembly Order:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 4 (central orange cylinder)
    Step2: Move block with index 2 (left blue rectangle)
    Step3: Move block with index 2 (right blue rectangle)
    Step4: Move block with index 13 (left roof piece)
    Step5: Move block with index 11 (right roof piece)
    Step6: Move block with index 15 (additional left roof piece)
}

The assembly creates a structure resembling a stylized house or building with a central tower and symmetrical sides. The blue blocks act as supporting elements while the orange pieces form the main structure and roof.
